  <h1>Classic Homemade Pancakes</h1>
  
  <p>A quick and easy recipe for fluffy, golden pancakes that are perfect for a cozy weekend breakfast.</p>

  <img src="https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/labs/recipe.jpg" alt="A stack of delicious pancakes topped with a pat of melting butter and maple syrup">

  <h2>Ingredients</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>1 cup all-purpose flour</li>
    <li>2 tablespoons white sugar</li>
    <li>1 cup milk (or buttermilk)</li>
    <li>1 large egg, beaten</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Instructions</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>In a large bowl, mix together the flour and sugar.</li>
    <li>Pour in the milk and beaten egg, then stir until smooth.</li>
    <li>Heat a lightly oiled griddle or frying pan over medium-high heat.</li>
    <li>Pour or scoop the batter onto the griddle, and brown on both sides. Serve hot!</li>
  </ol>

